==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ligneous
<hw>Lig"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g"n⟦esl⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>ligneus</ets>, fr. <ets>lignum</ets> wood. Cf.
<er>Lignous</er>.]</ety> <def>Made of wood; consisting of wood; of the
nature of, or resembling, wood; woody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It should be tried with shoots of vines and roots of red roses;
for it may be they, being of a more<qex>ligneous</qex> nature, will
incorporate with the tree itself.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ligneous marble</b></col>, <cd>wood coated or prepared so
as to resemble marble.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
